    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but like, when people talk about \"originalism\" being the standard, it sounds more like a legitimate legal method. but when people talk about the other side, it often sounds like they're just making up rules based on how they feel about guns today. don't you think there's a difference in how \"sound\" those two approaches are? like, isn't one more grounded in actual law and the other just more political?",
